The coefficients are related to Bernoulli numbers. Specifically, the coefficient of \( x^{2k+1} \) is \( \frac{(-1)^{k+1} 2^{2k} (2^{2k} - 1) B_{2k}}{(2k)!} \), where \( B_{2k} \) are Bernoulli numbers.
